Temporary traffic changes around the University of Wollongong and TAFE NSW will be in place from Monday 27 February 2023 for approximately six weeks, to minimise congestion for the start of the university year. 


The temporary traffic changes are as follows:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout, between 7.45am and 9.15am on weekdays. 
  • Traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted to the University Western Access route via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road during peak periods.  
  • Motorists accessing the M1 northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Avenue during peak periods will be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road.  

Bus access from University Avenue into Irvine Street will not be affected during diversions and outside peak periods traffic will continue to access the University via Irvine Street and Northfields Avenue.

Continuous closure northbound from 1130pm Sat 25 Feb to 7am Sun 5 Mar

Resident access will be maintained.

Temporary infrastructure works have started in Newcastle East to prepare for the Supercars Newcastle 500 event (10-12 March)

Road and park users should prepare for changes to traffic conditions over a nine-week period.

• Wharf Road from Watt Street to Horseshoe Beach Road is closed from 7am Wednesday 1 February until 5pm Friday 31st March, 2023

• Temporary closures or lane restrictions on Watt Street and Wharf Road

• Nobbys Beach east carpark will be closed until 5pm Friday 17 March

﻿• Queens Wharf Hotel West carpark closed until 5pm Friday 17 March


Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in place from 6am to 6pm Monday 27 to Friday 3 March;

  • Watt Street from Wharf Road past Church Street
  • Wharf Road from Queens Wharf Hotel to Watt Street
  • Church Street from Bolton Street to Watt Street

A clearway map can be found in the attachments.


Clearways are strict no parking zones for all vehicle types and apply even to local residents and businesses with parking permits or TfNSW Mobility Scheme permit holders. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.
